review_blob:
Goldenish color, spicy smell. Pretty tasty, pretty smooth but a little bit of alcohol bite on the end, time will do this one some favors. Nice spicy Belgian note as well, quite a bit of sweetness. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Beer pours very clear, seems like a good amount of carbonation. Very strange that a wit beer would be this clear. Overall not very representative of the style, seems strange, lacking in wheat, kinda muddled style-wise.
beer_name: Brau Brothers White Cap Crystal Wit

review_blob: Smells maybe a little like anise, a little boozy, and has a creamy coffee/roasty type smell. Hops also present in the aroma. Taste is very smooth. I wish this beer had a more rich/robust finish. I get more sweetness up front but not much in terms of bitterness/lingering sort of rich/roasty flavors I want in a stout. Its good, but its not that good.

Smell is a little boozy with roasty chocolate/coffee flavors.  Taste is a little on the sweeter side.  Mouthfeel is very smooth.  Very good flavors, time in the bottle (1 year+) should do this beer very well.
Smell is slightly bananaey with a really strong malt smell as well.  Pretty easy drinking, light, but wish it had a little more body to it.  Solid, well priced, but nothing stellar.

Smells past it's prime, if this beer had one.  Hop aroma is very muted, taste also muted and watery.  Not a good ipa, wouldn't buy or drink again.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Malty and spicy smell and taste.  Very belgiany like flavors.  Pretty balanced and smooth, maybe a little too spicy for me. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Smells a little funky, wild yeasty.  A little smokey.  Taste is nicely balanced smoke and a little tartness.  Pretty dry.  Overall pretty good

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Smells a little like bananas and belgiany like yeast.  Really good saison with a little spicyness to it.  A really tasty refreshing crisp beer 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Really good pale ale.  Citrusy aroma, citrusy taste.  Pretty balanced, not over the top bitter.  Really solid.

Smell is sweet and spicey.  I remember this being a lot more bready/malty when I had it last.  This one has kind of a bite to it and a lot of sweetness as well.  Not what I remember it being like at all.
Smell is very cherry.  Taste is also very cherry like.  Its maybe just a little too much fruit flavor for me, but this is a good fruit beer.

Smells very vanillay, roasty, and bourboney.  Taste has a sharp alcoholic bite to it, this would benefit from some more time in the bottle.  This is still a really tasty beer with oak, chocolate notes.  This beer poured out of the bottle and the appearance was great, super thick.

Aroma seems a little weak, earthy/musty kind of smell? Taste is really clean, nice bitter finish.  Not one of favorite double ipa's but still good.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Nice malty flavor/aroma.  This is how I prefer my amber/red ales, because this is pretty hoppy but not over the top.  Very enjoyable.
Smell is roasty and hoppy.  Taste is very bitter, dark chocolate/coffee like flavors as well as hop bitterness.  Alcohol at 9% is hidden well.  Really solid imperial stout.
Smells like floral hops, malt is present as well.  Not overly bitter.  This is a really tasty pale ale and I would drink it again.
beer_name: Odell St. Lupulin Extra Pale Ale

review_blob: Smells spicey, a little fruity, and a little boozy.  Taste is really smooth, some sort of spiceyness.

Not a lot of coffee smell, not as much as I had hoped.  Smells more like chocolate/roastey malts.  Taste is bitter, again not a lot of coffee.  Very smooth, pretty tasty, but I had higher hopes for this before I tried it.
Smells very malty, a little hoptty.  Caramel flavors.  Very sweet beer.  I struggled to drink my glass of this, and I was real thirsty at the time.  Not one I would buy again.
Smell is hoppy and malty.  Caramel/Toffee type aroma of the malt.  Taste is sweet with roasty/caramel flavors, bitter finish.  Really good, one of my favorite red ales.  Would never guess this is 9%.

This beer doesnt taste as bad as it smells, but the smell was overpowering with lemon.  Could smell a little bit of maltiness, but its not an appealing aroma.  Taste is about the same, but not as intense.  Not one I would buy or drink again.

Smells super chocolatey.  Really smooth chocolatey taste.  This is a really tasty beer.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Smell is very malty/toffee/caramel and English hops.  Taste has something off about it that I don't care for.  It his right up front, and is a little off putting.  There is a really solid beer here with some tweaking.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Smells winey and citrusy, maybe a hint of oak/wood.  Taste is very dry, tart and spicy.  Citrusy flavors as well.  Very tasty
Smell is very malty, pretty hoppy as well.  Has a nice bitterness but is well balanced.  Solid amber/red ale.

Smell is mostly citrusy hops.  No peach smell.  Not really tasting much peach either.  Taste is slightly sweet and hoppy.  A solid imperial IPA thats well balanced and very drinkable, just not worth the price based on other options out there.
beer_name: Odell Tree Shaker Imperial Peach IPA

review_blob: This does not taste like a 16% alcohol beer.  I may have guessed 9 or 10.  It is very smooth, belgiany flavors that are very subtle.  This is really drinkable and refreshing for the alcohol content.  Aroma is mostly spicey belgiany yeast.
Smell is more oakey than smokey.  Taste is very boozy and smokey.  I think this would be a great one to age so the flavors meld together more.

Smell is vanillaey and very roasty and chocolately.  Not getting a whole lot of coffee, very faint, overwhelmed by the other flavors.  Very boozy, strong finish.  Overall flavor is great.  This beer would be really good in a couple years I would think.  Will buy a couple to age.
Smells a little funky and a little lemony.  Also a little bit of spice.  Really balanced and drinkable.  Good mouthfeel, very sharp bubbly sensation.
Smell is funky and a little fruity.  Very dry beer.  Taste is slightly sour, little spicey, not so much in the fruit department for me, but thats not a bad thing.  Would drink again.
Pretty sweet and a little boozy.  Smell is fruity, maybe a little citrusy.  Not a huge fan.
beer_name: New Belgium Lips of Faith - Pluot

review_blob: Beer is on the sweeter side.  Bit of spice and bitterness as well.  Not really a whole lot going on here based on the number of ingredients.
beer_name: New Belgium Lips of Faith - Paardebloem

review_blob: Had a 2013 and a 2012 side by side.  Both versions smelled very roasty.  The older version did not have as much of a boozy smell.  Noticeable taste difference between the two, more so as it warmed.  The older version is much smoother, although both versions are very drinkable for 12%.  I prefer the older, smoother version because the malty dark flavors come through much more.
beer_name: Dark Horse Plead the 5th Imperial Stout

review_blob: Smell is very earthy and piney.  Taste is very crisp and clean.  Very light in color.  Taste isnt overly bitter for a double IPA, nicely balanced.  Really good.
Smells bready and malty.  Beer pours very clear with a white head.  Taste is very clean, some malt some hops, really refreshing.  Nothing crazy, but a solid lager.
beer_name: Toppling Goliath Dorothys New World Lager

review_blob: Smells very dark and roasty.  Coffee and chocolate smells, slightly hoppy.  Taste is bitter both from the hops and the roasted malts.  Pretty balanced though, very roasty flavors.  Really good black IPA.

Smells oaky and like whiskey.  Taste is very smooth, especially as this warms.  As far as barrel aged go, this one isnt that great.  Didnt really get much in terms of vanilla from this beer as the deScription says.
Smell is citrusy and piney with a strong malt nose as well.  Tastes pretty bitter, pretty balanced though, overall very tasty.  Solid Pale Ale.
beer_name: Great Lakes Burning River Pale Ale

review_blob: Smells very roasty and malty, slight hop flavor.  Taste is very malty, sweetness is balanced out by the roasted malts though.  Kind of thin feeling, could maybe be a little thicker.

Smells citrusy and hoppy.  Seems like this is boozier than 6.8%.  Taste is very one note for me.  A little more sweetness might be nice.  110 IBUs seems pretty high for the alcohol level.  Overall though, pretty good.
Smells very roasty, chocolately, and boozy.  Will be cellaring some for a while to see how it smooths out as it has a bit of an alcoholic bite to it.  Bitter and very thick.  Very rich, very smooth.

Smells tart, sour, and spicey. Very sour taste.  Strong flavor from the wine barrels as well.  This beer is super tart.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Bruery Terreux Sour in the Rye

review_blob: Not a ton going on in the aroma.  There is a caramel/malty smell with just a slight bit of hops.  Taste is very bitter though.  Also has an alcohol bite/burn at the end.  Could this potentially be ageable?  We will see....

Smells very tart.  A bit of fruitiness as well, a little wheat smell as well.  Taste is very tart/sour.  Very carbonated and refreshing.  Tastes slightly fruity, slightly sweet, and slightly sour.  Very easy drinking and tasty.

Smell is very earthy and belgiany.  It is really refreshing and light. Not a ton of Belgian flavor, has a little bit of spicyness, pretty dry.  A solid summer beer

Has an interesting banana and clove type flavor not normally found in barleywines.  The wheat flavor seems to give it a fuller body.  Has an alcoholic burn to it.  Might taste better with time, but not a huge fan.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Two Brothers Bare Tree Weiss Wine (2002 and later)

review_blob: Not a whole lot going on in the aroma.  Smell is very malty with a hint of nuttiness.  Taste is on the sweeter side but has a nuttiness to it as well.  I typically prefer a more roasty brown ale than this one.  Overall, just okay, cant see myself drinking this one again.

Smell is very malty and has plenty of belgian yeast in the aroma.  Tastes malty as well with the belgian yeast notes.  Dark fruit flavors as well come through.  Tastes a little bit woody, maybe like an oak characteristic.  Im not a huge fan of quads, but this one is pretty good.
